cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a task of extracting visually grounded paraphrases, which involves both natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the paper also discusses various methods for modeling the similarity between VGPs, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses neural network-based methods, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
